      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW KARA (5) carved over from wide out and boxed on strongly to finish 1.3 lengths away in second (22.30) behind Jill's Fantasy at Warrnambool. Capable of going well again. PELICAN'S SUNDAY (1) made light work of the tricky draw with a fast early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing third (22.58) at this track over 390m. Has a strong record from box 1, including three wins. Leading player again. JUST QUICKLY (3) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when seventh at Bendigo over 425m behind Chill Out Plate (24.77) in a Grade 5. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to her name from five starts. Key player if finds best. KRAKEN HUGGIE (2) can improve on an unplaced run here last time out.",
